reviews.text: Maytree is a wonderful nursery my daughter has been there since last year September she has come on leaps and bounds. The staff are wonderful very caring and genuinely care about the children. The nursery has lots of different things for the children to do. Highly recommend Maytree to all parents!! 5 stars from us

I love this nursery, the staff is absolutely brilliant!! Two of my sons have attended here and have had the best support from their keyworker and rest of staff. Everyone is so friendly and nurturing, I can truly see the positive influence attending maytree has provided for my boys! Their are so many courses and classes available for parents and community. I recommend it to everyone I meet at playgroups and will definitely be sending my third son here.

Our daughter goes to Maytree and really enjoys it. I have been impressed by the range of activities - for example over the last couple of months they have watched tadpoles grow into frogs, looked after caterpillars as they pupated and became butterflies, and incubated chicks. All the teachers are friendly and engaged, and we get a lot of feedback on how our daughter is doing (there's an app where we can see photos and clips of her day at nursery).

I'm more than happy to recommend Maytree Nusery school and children centre. My daughter is always excited to go in to meet her teachers and greeting the reception. The Nusery is a great and friendly place to be.

Angelique.
Freedom.

Very lovely nursery, very professional staff and beautiful new building! My son and my nephew love the teachers and the environment. I can see so many positive changes in their behaviour and I can honestly say that they learn something new every day.

address: 4 Allingham Rd, London SW4 8EG, United Kingdom
